{
  "name": "Mist AI Ops — Claude + Webhooks",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "mist-events",
        "responseMode": "onReceived",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567801",
      "name": "Mist Webhook Receiver",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-960, 200],
      "webhookId": "mist-events"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const body = $input.first().json.body || $input.first().json || {};\nconst topic = body.topic || 'unknown';\nconst HIGH_P = [\n  'device_down','switch_offline','gw_offline','ap_offline','gateway_offline',\n  'marvis_ap_offline','bad_cable','auth_failure_rate',\n  'rogue_ap','honeypot_ssid','vssid_spoofing'\n];\n\nif (topic === 'audits') {\n  const items = body.results || body.events || [body];\n  return items.filter(Boolean).map(e => ({\n    json: {\n      topic,\n      event_type: 'audit',\n      severity: 'info',\n      site_id: e.site_id || '',\n      site_name: e.site_name || '',\n      org_id: e.org_id || '',\n      device_mac: '',\n      device_name: '',\n      message: `${e.admin_name || 'Admin'}: ${e.message || ''}`.trim(),\n      count: 1,\n      timestamp: e.timestamp || Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000),\n      high_priority: false,\n      raw: e\n    }\n  }));\n}\n\nconst events = body.events || body.items || [];\nif (events.length === 0) {\n  return [{ json: {\n    topic,\n    event_type: 'ping',\n    severity: 'info',\n    site_id: '', site_name: 'n/a', org_id: '',\n    device_mac: '', device_name: '',\n    message: 'keepalive',\n    count: 0,\n    timestamp: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000),\n    high_priority: false,\n    raw: body\n  }}];\n}\n\nreturn events.map(e => ({\n  json: {\n    topic,\n    event_type: e.type || e.alarm_type || 'unknown',\n    severity: e.severity || 'info',\n    site_id: e.site_id || '',\n    site_name: e.site_name || 'unknown',\n    org_id: e.org_id || '',\n    device_mac: e.ap || e.mac || e.switch_mac || e.gateway_mac || '',\n    device_name: e.ap_name || e.switch_name || e.gateway_name || e.device_name || '',\n    message: e.message || e.reason || e.text || '',\n    count: e.count || 1,\n    timestamp: e.timestamp || Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000),\n    high_priority: HIGH_P.includes(e.type || e.alarm_type || ''),\n    raw: e\n  }\n}));"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567802",
      "name": "Normalize Event",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [-720, 200]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": false,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict",
            "version": 1
          },
          "combinator": "and",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.high_priority }}",
              "rightValue": true,
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "true",
                "singleValue": true
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567803",
      "name": "High Priority?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [-480, 200]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const e = $input.first().json;\n\nconst system = `You are Marvis AI Ops, an expert network operations assistant for Juniper Mist infrastructure. Your knowledge spans:\n- Mist AI/ML: Marvis Virtual Network Assistant, Dynamic Packet Capture, SLE metrics, Marvis Actions\n- Wireless: 802.11ax/WiFi 6/6E, RRM, 802.11r/k/v roaming, band steering, PSK/802.1X\n- Switching: EX Series, PoE budgets, port profiles, RSTP/MSTP, EVPN-VXLAN, LAG/LACP\n- WAN/SD-WAN: SRX, SSR, application-based steering, path quality monitoring\n- NAC: Mist Access Assurance, 802.1X, RADIUS, MAC Auth Bypass, ClearPass integration\n- Mist API: api.mist.com REST endpoints, webhook topics, tmunzer/mist_library (mistapi package)\n- HPE Aruba: Central, AOS-CX, GreenLake\n\nBe concise and actionable. Provide specific Mist API endpoints or CLI commands where helpful.`;\n\nconst user = `MIST EVENT ALERT — ${e.topic.toUpperCase()} / ${e.event_type.toUpperCase()}\n\nSite:     ${e.site_name} (${e.site_id})\nSeverity: ${e.severity} | Count: ${e.count}\nDevice:   ${e.device_name} [${e.device_mac}]\nTime:     ${new Date(e.timestamp * 1000).toISOString()}\n${e.message ? 'Details:  ' + e.message : ''}\n\nFull Payload:\n${JSON.stringify(e.raw, null, 2)}\n\nProvide:\n1. **Root Cause** — most likely explanation\n2. **Immediate Action** — specific Mist portal step or API call (include endpoint)\n3. **Verification** — how to confirm resolution\n4. **Prevention** — long-term recommendation\n5. **Priority**: P1 (critical/service down) | P2 (degraded) | P3 (informational)`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { system, user, event_context: e } }];"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567804",
      "name": "Build Analysis Prompt",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [-240, 80]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "x-api-key", "value": "={{ $env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}" },
            { "name": "anthropic-version", "value": "2023-06-01" },
            { "name": "content-type", "value": "application/json" }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n  \"max_tokens\": 2048,\n  \"system\": {{ JSON.stringify($json.system) }},\n  \"messages\": [{ \"role\": \"user\", \"content\": {{ JSON.stringify($json.user) }} }]\n}",
        "options": { "timeout": 60000 }
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567805",
      "name": "Claude Analyze Event",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [0, 80],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const r = $input.first().json;\nconst text = r.content?.[0]?.text || r.error?.message || 'Claude analysis unavailable';\nconst pm = text.match(/\\*?\\*?Priority\\*?\\*?[:\\s]+(P[123])/i) || text.match(/\\b(P[123])\\b/);\nconst priority = pm ? pm[1] : 'P2';\nreturn [{ json: { analysis: text, priority, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() } }];"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567806",
      "name": "Parse Analysis",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [240, 80]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "http://mist-api:8000/webhook/n8n/analysis",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={{ JSON.stringify({ analysis: $json.analysis, priority: $json.priority, timestamp: $json.timestamp, event_context: $('Build Analysis Prompt').first().json.event_context }) }}",
        "options": {
          "timeout": 5000,
          "response": { "response": { "neverError": true } }
        }
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567807",
      "name": "Push to Tatooine",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [480, 80],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const e = $input.first().json;\nconsole.log('LOW_PRIORITY', JSON.stringify({ ts: new Date().toISOString(), type: e.event_type, topic: e.topic, site: e.site_name, device: e.device_name }));\nreturn [{ json: {\n  analysis: `Low priority event: **${e.event_type}** on topic \\`${e.topic}\\`\\n\\n**Site:** ${e.site_name}\\n**Device:** ${e.device_name || 'n/a'} [${e.device_mac || 'n/a'}]\\n**Message:** ${e.message || 'n/a'}`,\n  priority: 'P3',\n  timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n  event_context: e\n} }];"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567808",
      "name": "Log Low Priority",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [-240, 320]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "http://mist-api:8000/webhook/n8n/analysis",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={{ JSON.stringify($json) }}",
        "options": {
          "timeout": 5000,
          "response": { "response": { "neverError": true } }
        }
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567809",
      "name": "Push Low to Tatooine",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [0, 320],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },

    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "mist-chat",
        "responseMode": "lastNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567810",
      "name": "Chat Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-960, 900],
      "webhookId": "mist-chat"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const b = $input.first().json.body || $input.first().json || {};\nconst orgId = b.org_id || process.env.MIST_DEFAULT_ORG_ID || '';\n\nconst system = `You are Marvis AI Ops for Juniper Mist networks. Help operators query and manage their Mist environment.\n\nAvailable actions (use when the query requires live network data):\n- get_sites: list all org sites\n- get_devices: list devices at a site (needs site_id)\n- get_clients: list active wireless clients at a site (needs site_id)\n- get_alarms: get active org alarms\n\nRespond ONLY with valid JSON, no markdown code fences:\n{\"intent\": \"brief description\", \"action\": \"action_name or null\", \"params\": {\"site_id\": \"if needed\"}, \"response\": \"your reply to the operator\", \"needs_confirmation\": false}`;\n\nconst history = (b.history || []).map(h => ({ role: h.role, content: h.content }));\nconst messages = [\n  ...history,\n  { role: 'user', content: `Org: ${orgId}\\nSite: ${b.site_id || 'not specified'}\\nQuery: ${b.query || b.message || ''}` }\n];\n\nreturn [{ json: { system, messages, org_id: orgId, site_id: b.site_id || '' } }];"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567811",
      "name": "Build Chat Prompt",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [-720, 900]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "x-api-key", "value": "={{ $env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}" },
            { "name": "anthropic-version", "value": "2023-06-01" },
            { "name": "content-type", "value": "application/json" }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n  \"max_tokens\": 1024,\n  \"system\": {{ JSON.stringify($json.system) }},\n  \"messages\": {{ JSON.stringify($json.messages) }}\n}",
        "options": { "timeout": 30000 }
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567812",
      "name": "Claude Chat",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [-480, 900],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const r = $input.first().json;\nconst raw = r.content?.[0]?.text || r.error?.message || '{\"response\": \"Claude unavailable\", \"action\": null}';\nlet intent = {};\ntry {\n  intent = JSON.parse(raw.replace(/```json\\n?|```/g, '').trim());\n} catch(e) {\n  intent = { action: null, response: raw, needs_confirmation: false, params: {} };\n}\n\nconst orgId = $('Build Chat Prompt').first().json.org_id;\nconst siteId = intent.params?.site_id || $('Build Chat Prompt').first().json.site_id || '';\n\nconst apiUrls = {\n  get_sites:   `https://api.mist.com/api/v1/orgs/${orgId}/sites`,\n  get_devices: `https://api.mist.com/api/v1/sites/${siteId}/devices?type=all`,\n  get_clients: `https://api.mist.com/api/v1/sites/${siteId}/stats/clients`,\n  get_alarms:  `https://api.mist.com/api/v1/orgs/${orgId}/alarms/search?limit=50`\n};\n\nconst api_url = intent.action ? (apiUrls[intent.action] || null) : null;\nreturn [{ json: { ...intent, api_url, org_id: orgId, site_id: siteId } }];"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567813",
      "name": "Parse Chat Intent",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [-240, 900]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": false,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict",
            "version": 1
          },
          "combinator": "and",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.api_url }}",
              "rightValue": "",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "notEmpty",
                "singleValue": true
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567814",
      "name": "Has API Action?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [0, 900]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "={{ $json.api_url }}",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "Authorization", "value": "=Token {{ $env.MIST_API_TOKEN }}" }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "response": { "response": { "neverError": true } }
        }
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567815",
      "name": "Execute Chat API Call",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [240, 780],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const intent = $('Parse Chat Intent').first().json;\nconst apiData = $input.first().json;\nreturn [{ json: {\n  response: intent.response,\n  action: intent.action,\n  params: intent.params,\n  data: apiData,\n  needs_confirmation: intent.needs_confirmation || false\n} }];"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567816",
      "name": "Build Chat Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [480, 780]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={{ JSON.stringify($json) }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567817",
      "name": "Chat Respond With Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [720, 780]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const intent = $('Parse Chat Intent').first().json;\nreturn [{ json: {\n  response: intent.response,\n  action: null,\n  params: {},\n  data: null,\n  needs_confirmation: intent.needs_confirmation || false\n} }];"
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567818",
      "name": "Build Chat Response No Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [240, 1020]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={{ JSON.stringify($json) }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567819",
      "name": "Chat Respond No Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [480, 1020]
    },

    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "mist-api",
        "responseMode": "lastNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c1a2b3d4-e5f6-4890-ab01-001234567820",
      "name": "Mist API Proxy",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-960, 1600],
      "webhookId": "mist-api"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
